WE ARE LENDICO

The team at Lendico stands for combining sophisticated technology, in-depth finance understanding, and years of experience with streamlined processes and the courage to explore new things. We’re better – and that is not only valued by our customers but also recognized with multiple awards by the finance industry.

ING & Lendico

With ING on our side, we focus on what we do best: offer financing solutions for small and medium sized companies – fast, straightforward, inexpensive.

For the past 50 years, ING has proved in Germany that they are different. We’re doing the same – just not quite as long. That’s why we are convinced that ING’s corporate strategy in Germany and Lendico’s digital, very efficient business model complement each other well and that together we can grow faster.

Tasks

As a Data Marketing Analyst, you will not only work on data processes that support marketing strategies but also analyze touch-points in order to generate insights to improve the customer journey. You will be working collaboratively with Marketing managers and business intelligence team to provide effective and valuable data.


Build, maintain and communicate reports and dashboards to track Marketing’s key performance indicators against business plan;
Undertaking deep-dive analyses of online campaign performances to put forward hypotheses and recommendations for future initiatives;
Contribute to the firm’s measurement space by combining creative problem solving with analytical rigor to drive actionable insights;
Work on Attribution Model,
Work closely together with Online Marketing managers, Web & CRO (Conversion Rate Optimization) manager, UX, BI and other teams on online marketing-related adhoc analysis;
Work with BI team to maintain and keep improving our future Marketing data mart.

Requirements


3+ years’ experience in an analytics role;
Experience with web-based dashboards (such as Looker, PowerBI, Tableau & Qlik);
Proficiency in Microsoft Office suite;
Working experience with Google Analytics;
SQL, Python or R know-how as a plus;
Experience with developing presentations or platforms to concisely illustrate complex quantitative analysis and deliver strategic recommendations;
Desirable work experience in FinTech domain, bank or some other financial sector;
Experience in agile and lean product management methods;
Experience with digital marketing acquisition channels, particularly SEM, SEO and paid social, CRM/email;
Fluent in English, good German-skills would be a plus.

Benefits


An unlimited contract
A steep learning curve in an innovative industry; including plenty of responsibility and conceptual freedom
Extensive opportunities for personal and professional growth
An international team of experts who inspire and support you
An easily accessible and modern workplace
Various benefits, from BVG-Ticket (AB) to further education budget to lunch subsidies
Regular get-togethers, team-building events, barbecues, and parties
Typical start-up perks: soft drinks and snacks for free, language classes for German and English, company pension scheme, etc.

Ivanhoé Cambridge develops and invests in high-quality real estate properties, projects and companies that are shaping the urban fabric in dynamic cities around the world. It does so responsibly, with a view to generate long-term performance. Ivanhoé Cambridge is committed to creating living spaces that foster the well-being of people and communities, while reducing its environmental footprint.

Vertically integrated in Canada, Ivanhoé Cambridge invests internationally alongside strategic partners and major real estate funds that are leaders in their markets. Through subsidiaries and partnerships, the Company holds interests in more than 1,000 buildings, primarily in the industrial and logistics, office, residential and retail sectors. Ivanhoé Cambridge held close to C$65 billion in real estate assets as at December 31, 2018 and is a real estate subsidiary of the Caisse de dépôt et placement du Québec (cdpq.com), one of Canada's leading institutional fund managers. For more information: ivanhoecambridge.com.


Department : Berlin Office

Position type : Salaried

Specific accountabilities

The team is responsible for all investments related to the acquisition of properties in Europe in accordance with the Company’s strategic plan. It also identifies investment opportunities with the potential to earn the Company better risk-adjusted returns. Germany is an important European market and follow a structured expansion strategy and Ivanhoé Cambridge is committed to further growth of the German operation and platform. There are already more than € 0.5bn Assets under Management in Germany and strategic partnerships on the ground and this will keep growing.


The incumbent assists his/her manager and the investment team in actively managing the real estate portfolio. To this end, he or she conducts analyses, issues recommendations and executes real estate investments in target markets in collaboration with strategic operational partners. In collaboration with the Paris Analysts team, the main duties include the following:
Sourcing
Stay abreast of calls for tenders and conduct the necessary preliminary analyses;
Carry out studies and analyses;
Monitor the validation of trading decisions;
Facilitate own network to source deals.


Valuation

Perform the necessary preliminary analyses, make financial arrangements and generate financial models;
Work with partners and consultants to gather legal and tax data to help with assessing an investment’s feasibility;
Compile all financial and market data needed to analyze files (investment opportunities/ Deals) based on Ivanhoé Cambridge’s investment criteria;
Communicate directly with brokers/sellers and other market participants to obtain documentation or information necessary for reviewing investment projects;
Put together decision-making documents, especially in preparation for committee and board meetings (follow established procedures and produce the required documents, such as investment prospectuses).


Support for Asset Management Policy

Analyze operations statistics (occupancy rates, sales, leasing activities);
Put together financial data, including annual and quarterly financial forecasts;
Determine the feasibility of initiatives using financial analysis and cash flow projections in light of current trends and market outlook for assets;
Identify, in conjunction with the relevant manager, assets targeted for disposition and the corresponding conditions.


Due Diligence

Plan, coordinate and participate in the due diligence process, ensuring that it goes smoothly;
Coordinate with stakeholders, both external (legal/tax/technical consultants, partners, brokers, asset managers, etc.) and internal (portfolio management, financial services, taxation, legal affairs, asset management, risk management, insurance and development), to gather information and conduct analyses relevant to investments while adhering to transaction deadlines;
Evaluate the risks and challenges raised during the due diligence process and discuss the relevant points with partners and stakeholders;
Negotiate contracts;
Prepare legal paperwork with the help of internal departments, lawyers and external consultants and submit for signature;
Handle post-closing procedures;
Coordinate investment-related reporting and ensure proper classification and archiving of all necessary documents according to Ivanhoé Cambridge’s internal standards.


Key requirements
Master’s degree (Bac + 5) in finance, accounting, auditing or management;
2 to 5 years of relevant experience in a comparable position;
Energetic, proactive, self-motivated and disciplined;
Excellent analytical and processing skills;
Professional, loyal, transparent and accountable;
Leader and team player interested in working with a small group of people inside of a large organization;
Organized and methodical with a high level of financial and technical expertise;
Creative, adept at problem-solving and an excellent negotiator with presence and conviction;
Available to travel abroad for business;
In-depth knowledge of Microsoft Office suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint);
Strong communication and interpersonal skills with a sense of initiative, an attention to detail and the ability to prioritize;
Experience assisting with project management at all stages is an asset;
Ability to multitask, work independently and in a team, and perform under pressure in a dynamic environment;
Fluency in English is a must. French would be an important asset.


If you're interested in this challenge, please submit the English version of your resume in order to facilitate the screening.


You have everything to gain!

When you join the Ivanhoé Cambridge team, you are eligible for employment benefits and a pension plan that are among the best in the industry. Our many health and wellness programs encourage you to balance your work and personal lives and fulfil your desire for social involvement, while maintaining a healthy lifestyle. At Ivanhoé Cambridge, you will have many opportunities to develop your skills and thrive professionally, in Canada or elsewhere in the world. Our initiatives aimed at creating an exceptional working environment that inspires our employees to give the best of themselves elevated Ivanhoé Cambridge into the ranks of 100 Top Employers in Canada.
Ivanhoé Cambridge’s commitment to diversity and inclusion spans the breadth of its operations. Accommodations are available upon request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process. We take pride in creating a working environment where everyone is set up for success. Please advise us of any accommodations needed to ensure you have access to a fair and equitable process. Any information received relating to accommodation will be addressed confidentially.

As a part of Strategic Growth Businesses (SGB) unit of Amadeus, Travel Audience is the world’s leading data-driven travel advertising platform. The business unit harnesses the power of cutting edge machine learning practices to connect the leading performance-oriented advertisers with the biggest network of publishers, reaching millions of travellers. The strategy is to optimize advertising across the entire traveller journey, identify and create new audiences, and increase our partners reach, relevance and booking volumes.

We are looking for an experienced Manager for our Data Analytics team composed by Data and Business Analysts. You will lead a team in supporting this exciting digital marketing vision while working closely with Data Scientists and Engineers and Business stakeholders.


What you will do:

Manage a Data & Business Analytics team: A team performing a variety of functions, including data visualisation for self-service, internal and external customer reports, insights analysis and business analysis working with BigQuery, Tableau, Airflow and advanced SQL. You will set smart goals with the team that balance long term effective delivery with quality and team engagement. You will be responsible for coaching, mentoring and developing the team as well as partnering with the People & Culture team in managing talent life cycle from Attraction to Retention.
Delivery: You will be accountable for the team delivering value to the company and will work intimately with our product team and business stakeholders to ensure both the effective planning of new visualisation and reporting features and delivery of business insights, metrics and KPIs. You will advocate for technical best practices, data integrity and quality, whilst driving long term efficiency and continuity of service. You will participate in improving Engineering wide delivery process and governance as part of the Product and Tech Leadership Team.
Technical Expertise: You will perform deep analysis of business metrics on behalf of internal business stakeholders and develop and monitor business KPIs based on performance data. You will ensure the quality, stability and evolution of our reporting and visualisation tools with an emphasis on providing a self-service model to internal stakeholders and external clients. You will define, in collaboration with the data science and engineering teams, the standards for data modelling, consistency and availability and help ensure our systems are running correctly and efficiently. You will keep abreast of industry trends and knowledge within the Data Engineering domain and drive innovation in the team.

Why join us?

As part of our team, you will work in a highly motivated environment with flat hierarchies and short decision-making processes. You'll have a lot of freedom to contribute your own ideas, implement them and work with a modern tech stack. We offer you:

The interesting role of managing a talented Analytics team in an organisation where data is at its core;
The opportunity to drive business growth and truly having an impact on the business;
The opportunity to work with large amounts of data;
A dynamic industry where you handle new challenges every day;
An environment where you are encouraged to research, explore and try new ways of doing things;
An open and dynamic culture that supports great work-life balance.

About you:

You will have solid all-round technical experience and proven expertise in at least one domain as data, insights or business analytics or data visualisation.
You can perform deep data analyses using SQL, Analytics tools such as Tableau or a language such as Python;
You have successfully led a team before and enjoy managing people;
You can mentor and coach, develop knowledge sharing initiatives and plan long-term personal/team development;
You have worked with data analytics and visualisation tools such as Tableau, Qlik etc. and can produce customer-facing reports that are intuitive to use yet feature-rich with a good understanding of customer requirements and with a view to promoting a self-service workflow to business stakeholders;
You can plan, prioritise and troubleshoot;
You are a great communicator and you can adapt your message to different stakeholders;
You can be strategic on how we will use our tools and enable your stakeholders
You have a holistic understanding of IT systems, Data warehousing and ETL pipelines;
You can work with the Data Engineer team in scoping new requirements for data storage, structure and quality;
You can drive innovation by updating yourself and applying best practices in the team’s work dynamics;
You can quickly understand the business domain, AdTech knowledge is a plus;
You can speak, write and express yourself in English in a professional context;

We are eagerly awaiting your application and looking forward to starting our journey together!

Meet André, one of our Engineering Managers and your future colleague!

Systems Metabolic Engineer
Full-time – Berlin, Germany

What we do

We are harnessing machine learning to revolutionize the bioeconomy. Bioinformatics and machine learning will enable numerous steps in synthetic biological processes and generate novel solutions for a sustainable future. Come join our venture to engineer the tools of the future economy. You will be one of the early employees, having an outsized impact, shaping the company through your efforts, scientific experience and industry expertise. We are incubated at Merantix, an AI Venture Studio which conceptualizes, builds and scales machine learning companies. Merantix is distinct in its attraction of world-class talents, trust from European´s leading organizations and dynamic culture across its ventures. Our team is made up of 60 engineers, scientists, and entrepreneurs from leading universities. Many of us hold a Ph.D. and gained experience at top-tier tech companies.

We are looking for a Systems Metabolic Engineer to enhance our team and to help us build the next generation of machine learning applications for the bioeconomy.

Your Role

You will use a combination of Genome-scale metabolic models (GSSM) and machine learning to build the most accurate organismal models to date. Working with our academic and industry partners, you will create ‘in silico’ models to aid in strain optimization. Additionally, you will help build infrastructure that enables data gathering and experimental planning at scale. The tasks are diverse and non-repetitive, as we constantly receive new projects from industrial and academic partners. Successful projects will be highly automated via clean, maintainable code. You will work in a team with biologists, bioinformaticians, machine learning experts and business analysts to create the newest tools to enable the bioeconomy.

Your main responsibilities will include:

Augment and develop current GSSMs using the latest in machine learning techniques;

Work closely with our academic and industrial partners to design experiments and steer the venture’s part in the collaboration;

Deploy models at partners as needed;

Keep up-to-date with the latest advances in the field;

Drive long-term success by building or integrating new technologies;

Manage multiple projects allowing us to deliver useful tools to our partners as well as internal proof of concepts;

Develop a scientific and technical vision of the venture together with a collaborative, interdisciplinary and entrepreneurial team.


Qualifications

We define ourselves by a culture of ownership and cooperation. We are looking for driven, capable, visionary and prudent talents with proven track records of personal, academic and professional achievement:

MSc or PhD in Chemical or Biological Engineering with experience in metabolomics and machine learning;

Exceptional competence in GSSMs and experience in applied machine learning and software engineering and its application in biology;

Mathematics background, experience with supervised learning, dynamic systems and control theory, ODE solvers and multivariate statistics;

Experience with several of the following technologies: Google Cloud Platform, TensorFlow, Apache Beam, Google Cloud ML, Docker, or PyTorch;

Passion for exploration and execution of ‘proof of concept’ projects;

Intense drive to learn new skills and utilize new technologies;

Ability to work in a fast paced environment, dealing with uncertainty and building something from the ground up;

Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills.


Working at Merantix

Our hierarchy is flat and communication direct, which means that we operate and learn fast, as a team. You are a great fit for our team if this describes you:

Entrepreneurial mindset: creative, focused, and not easily discouraged;

Ability to work in a fast-paced, highly innovative environment where ambiguity is the norm;

Excellent analytical problem-solving skills, with the ability to step back and contextualize the problem and its root;

Independent but cooperative mindset;

Strong organizational and multitasking skills with the ability to prioritize appropriately and effectively;

Love what you do (and own it).

In addition to a competitive salary and equity package, you can expect the following:


Flexible working hours as we believe in ownership and trust;

Learning & Development Program for all our team members;

Regular team events and intensive exchange with all Merantix companies;

Free drinks, snacks and breakfast.

We are an equal-opportunity employer and value diversity. We consider all applications equally regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, or gender identity. We strongly encourage individuals from groups traditionally underrepresented in tech to apply, and we can help with immigration.

