Join our R&D Team as Senior Data Engineer!

By joining us, you will be combining your passion for technology and have a direct impact on the lives of millions of travellers, while also helping travel audience in becoming the global leader in data-driven advertising for the entire travel industry.

What you will do:

You'll be part of a team responsible for the design, development and maintenance of our data processing streaming pipelines in Google Cloud Dataflow developed using Spark;
You'll work closely with the Data Scientists and Data Analysts, providing them with access to the data and support they need to analyse, train and deploy machine-learning models;
You'll own the full development and operations cycle of a product, whilst helping to ensure our systems are running correctly and efficiently;
You'll use industry-proven tools such as git, and practices such as CI/CD in an agile setup;
You'll be joining a cross-functional team. Aside from data engineers, our teams have Go Engineers, Data Scientists, Data Analysts, DevOps Engineers, and Frontend Engineers.


Why join us?

As part of our team, you will work in a highly motivated environment, with equal opportunities, flat hierarchies and short decision-making processes. You’ll have a lot of freedom to contribute your own ideas and implement them.

The opportunity to drive business growth and truly having an impact on the business;
A fast-paced industry where you handle new problems every day;
An environment where you are encouraged to research, explore and try new ways of doing things;
An open and dynamic culture that supports great work-life balance, while being part of Amadeus, the biggest travel tech company in the world.

About you:


You love Scala – either as Scala developer or a Python/Java developer willing to self-learn a new language;
You have practical experience with one or more distributed data processing frameworks such as Spark, Apache Beam, Google Cloud Dataflow, Flink, Storm or similar;
You care deeply about software best practices and are dedicated to ensuring quality via testing, benchmarking and peer review;
You have experience of using a pub/sub or message queue technology such as Kafka;
You understand the theory behind different database technologies and data storage practices enough to make informed choices and match appropriate technologies to a given use-case;
You dedicate yourself to continue learning and improving and you enjoy helping others grow around you;
You’re eager to understand the business logic of the company and the meaning of the data they work with;
You can speak, write and express yourself in English – our company’s working language – in a professional context;
You feel at home collaborating in a workplace which is international, diverse, evolving and continually innovating.

We are awaiting your application and looking forward to starting our journey together!

Meet Ziyad, one of our Data Engineers

We are searching for an entrepreneurial, dynamic Global Supply Chain Analyst for our Berlin head office.
If you are passionate about data and processes as well as designing tools and models while having the opportunity to make a strong impact on improving business operations - we are looking forward to your application!
Marley Spoon brings delicious, fresh and simple cooking back to the people. Every week our chefs develop new inspiring and delicious recipes. Our customers choose the dishes they would like to cook and we deliver recipes and all ingredients that they need. We are a rapidly growing company operating in US, Australia and Europe, spreading over 7 countries with more than 900 employees. We leverage technology to re-invent the global food supply chain to reduce non-ethical food waste.
But in the end it's simple: We started Marley Spoon because we love cooking and we love eating!

Responsibilities
Build and develop Supply Chain supporting tools, used globally, with a major focus on forecasting and replenishment models;
Gather, manipulate and transform data from different sources to generate reports and improve the efficiency and accuracy of several workflows in our Supply Chain;
Work with different teams (Culinary, Procurement, Production, Data, Finance, Customer Insights, etc.) to increase the business value our Supply Chain tools: from concept design to implementation and adoption by key users in their critical processes;
Support, train and advise other teams and colleagues on analytics inquiries, driving operational excellence across the board;
Take an active role in shaping our Supply Chain Analytics strategy, by continuously assessing and challenging both business and technology landscapes.
Requirements
Degree in Engineering, Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science or Information Management;
Multiple years of experience in an analytical role;
Proven operational background, supply chain related preferably, with expertise on data models and database design development;
Proficiency with ETL processes and Data relationship models and structures, using SQL and Javascript;
Experience in building and maintaining a diversified pool of tools used by different stakeholders: Excel, Google Sheets, BI tools, Platform app builders (e.g. Zoho Creator);
Process and information flow understanding;
Strong problem solving and multi-tasking skills with great attention to detail;
Strong communication skills and ability to manage different stakeholders through the entire project life cycle (from concept design to delivery and maintenance of tools or reporting);
Entrepreneurial mindset, who loves identifying opportunities and getting things done.
Benefits
From your first day you have a real impact on shaping and developing our operations;
True ownership, real responsibilities, and strong opportunities for growth;
Flat hierarchies and a great team spirit;
A challenge in a fast-growing company with great development opportunities;
A dynamic start-up team with big ambitions;
Share options - participate in our journey;
Awesome Food.
